The paper presents a new model for representing data using a mixture of simplices, which has applications in machine learning and computer vision. The paper discusses the use of the model for classification and generative modeling, which suggests that it could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the geometric properties of the simplices, which suggests that it could fall under the category of cs.GR (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the model for reconstruction and regularization, which suggests that it could fall under the category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
